**Ex-Trump Adviser Wants Him to Reverse 30-Year-Old Nuclear Weapons Policy**
Former White House National Security Advisor Robert O'Brien, who served under Donald Trump's administration, has written an essay in Foreign Affairs magazine, urging Trump to reverse a 30-year-old nuclear weapons policy. O'Brien argues that the US should resume live-testing nuclear weapons and increase production of uranium-235 and plutonium-239, the primary fissile isotopes of nuclear weapons. This comes as tensions between the US and other nations remain heightened amid Russia's ongoing war with Ukraine. Trump, who is the presumptive Republican nominee for president in the 2024 election, has not commented on the recommendations.
