**The Prolongation of the Ukraine War is Flirting with a Nuclear Catastrophe**
The prolongation of the Ukraine war is flirting with a nuclear catastrophe. The probability of a nuclear catastrophe is low, but it is still present. Therefore, de-escalation is necessary. The war in Ukraine has been ongoing for three years, with hundreds of thousands of casualties on both sides. The West has been supporting Ukraine with financial aid, military advice, and modern weapons, hoping to push Russia back to its 2014 borders. This is an illusion that cannot be put into words. Similarly, the claim by Western politicians that Putin will take over more of Europe if he is not defeated in Ukraine is unfounded and lacks evidence. The recent attacks on Russian nuclear warning radar stations are particularly irresponsible and bring us closer to a nuclear war. NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg has announced an 18% increase in military spending in Europe and Canada in 2024, with two-thirds going to US manufacturers. Meanwhile, the International Campaign to Abolish Nuclear Weapons has announced that global spending on nuclear weapons will increase by 13% in 2023, with the US leading the way. The US has increased its spending on nuclear weapons by 45% over the past five years, followed by the UK with 43%. The article concludes that it is time to change the policy towards Ukraine and stop the escalation before it is too late.
