**Sipri Report: More Operational Nuclear Weapons**
According to the Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (Sipri), the number of operational nuclear weapons has increased in the past year. While some warheads are being decommissioned and the global total number of nuclear weapons is decreasing, more warheads are being kept operational. The report highlights a concerning trend, with experts expecting it to continue and even accelerate in the coming years. The nine countries possessing nuclear weapons are the USA, Russia, the UK, France, China, India, Pakistan, North Korea, and Israel, with the USA and Russia holding approximately 90% of the total nuclear warheads. Germany does not possess any nuclear weapons. The transparency of nuclear forces has decreased since the Russian invasion of Ukraine in February 2022, according to Sipri experts.
