**Zakharova Calls on Poland to Reveal Information on Nord Stream Sabotage**
Russian Foreign Ministry official Maria Zakharova has called on Polish Foreign Minister Radosław Sikorski to reveal information about the sabotage of the Nord Stream gas pipelines and the role of the US in the incident. Zakharova made the statement in an interview with the newspaper Izvestia, following Sikorski's comments in The Guardian, where he said that if Russia uses nuclear weapons, the US would strike Russian military positions in the special operation zone. The explosions on the Nord Stream and Nord Stream 2 pipelines occurred on September 26, 2022, and Germany, Denmark, and Sweden suspected it was a targeted act of sabotage. The Russian General Prosecutor's Office has launched an investigation into an act of international terrorism. The Nord Stream AG operator has stated that it is impossible to estimate the repair timeline due to the unprecedented damage to the pipelines.
